# A Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer named Ray
Who boogied the nights away
    With sequins so bright
    And moves out of sight
The disco ball followed his sway

The DJ would spin with such flair
As dancers with fabulous hair
    In platforms so high
    Reached up to the sky
And strutted without any care

When morning would finally arrive
The night owls would stumble outside
    With glitter and gleam
    And memories to keep
From when disco was gloriously alive

deepseek
________

**Disco Delight**  

There once was a dance floor so bright,  
Where folks boogied all through the night.  
With glitter and flair,  
They'd strut without care—  
Oh, disco was pure dynamite!  

The bass line would thump with a beat,  
As dancers moved fast with their feet.  
In platform shoes tall,  
They’d party through all—  
No rhythm could ever be beat!  

But soon came the end of the trend,  
When rock took the stage once again.  
Yet disco still shines,  
In nostalgic minds—  
A flashback we’d all love to spin!

